Q2. Inductor loss calculation:
Buck converter inductor: L=47µH, I_load=8A, ΔI_L=1.5A, f_s=100kHz.
Inductor parameters: R_DC=12mΩ, R_AC=25mΩ (at 100kHz, accounting for skin/proximity effects), Steinmetz k=0.04, α=1.4, β=2.5, V_core=4000mm³, B_peak=0.18T.
(a) DC copper loss: I_load²×R_DC
(b) AC copper loss: (ΔI_L/(2√3))²×R_AC
(c) Total copper loss
(d) Core loss using Steinmetz equation
(e) Total inductor loss and ratio of core to copper loss. Is the inductor design copper-loss dominated or core-loss dominated at this frequency?
